---
name: execute-spec
description: Run a spec through the SDD workflow. Auto-advances to the next pending spec if the given one is already complete.
---

Configuration:
- SPEC_NAME: 001-initial-setup

## Phase 0 — Resolve Active Spec

Before doing anything else, determine the actual spec to execute:

1. Read .specify/specs/{SPEC_NAME}/tasks.md
2. Count pending (- [ ]) and completed (- [x]) tasks
3. Apply this logic:

If all tasks are [x]:
  - This spec is COMPLETE. Do not re-implement it.
  - Scan .specify/specs/ in numeric order (001, 002, 003...)
  - Find the first spec with at least one pending task (- [ ])
  - Set ACTIVE_SPEC = that folder
  - Announce: "Spec {SPEC_NAME} is complete. Advancing to <ACTIVE_SPEC>."

If pending tasks exist:
  - Set ACTIVE_SPEC = {SPEC_NAME}
  - Announce: "Executing {SPEC_NAME} — <N> pending tasks found."

If no pending spec exists anywhere:
  - Announce: "All specs complete. Running consistency check."
  - Go to Phase 4. Stop after check.

All subsequent phases use ACTIVE_SPEC.

## Phase 1 — Mandatory Reading Order

1. .github/copilot-instructions.md
2. .specify/memory/constitution.md
3. .specify/specs/<ACTIVE_SPEC>/spec.md
4. .specify/specs/<ACTIVE_SPEC>/plan.md
5. .specify/specs/<ACTIVE_SPEC>/tasks.md

## Phase 2 — Pre-flight Check

1. Inspect codebase state relevant to ACTIVE_SPEC.
2. Identify pending tasks that may already be partially implemented.
3. Verify before marking [x] — do not re-implement what already exists correctly.

## Phase 3 — Execution

1. Execute pending tasks (- [ ]) in sequence.
2. Mark [x] only when truly complete.
3. Only modify files within scope defined by spec.md and plan.md.
4. Do not introduce anything prohibited by constitution.md.
5. Stop and surface any contradiction between documents.

## Phase 4 — Consistency Check

1. Verify each acceptance criterion in spec.md against actual code.
2. Verify implemented structure matches plan.md decisions.
3. Verify no (- [ ]) tasks remain.
4. Verify no code contradicts constitution.md.
Report any inconsistency. Do not silently pass a failing check.

## Required Output

Active spec : <ACTIVE_SPEC>
Reason      : [executing | auto-advanced from {SPEC_NAME} | all complete]

Tasks completed this session: <list>
Tasks remaining: <list or "none">
Files created or modified: <list>
Consistency check: PASSED | FAILED (<reason>)
Next action: <run execute-spec with next spec | run sdd sync>
